            . I am a watch and clock maker. About eight or nine o'clock on the morning of the 6th of September, the prisoner brought me a silver table spoon to sell; I asked her if it was her own - she said it was, and that her name was Williams - there was a W on the spoon; I bought it of her at 4 s. 9 d. per ounce as old silver, and gave her 8 s. 9 1/2 d. - I am sure she is the person.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am sorry for what I have done.</p>
